net.sourceforge.gxl
Class GXLAttributedElement

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--net.sourceforge.gxl.GXLElement
        |
        +--net.sourceforge.gxl.GXLAttributedElement
Direct Known Subclasses:
GXLAttr, GXLRelend, GXLTypedElement
public abstract class GXLAttributedElement
extends GXLElement

Superclass for all GXLElements that can be attributed using attr elements.

Attributes on GXL elements are set by adding attr elements to the attributed element. Thus to give a node the attribute color with a value of blue you create a GXLAttr element, specifying it's name as color and it's value as a GXLString containing the string blue.

The UML definition of GXL defines that all attributed elements may contain the attribute id resulting in the methods getID and setID being in this class. It should however be noted that the element relend is an exception to this and trying to set the id of a relend will result in an exception.

See Also:
GXLAttr, GXLValue
